HEADWORD: Thibet cloth
<hw>Thib"et cloth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A fabric made of
coarse goat's hair; a kind of camlet.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A kind of
fine woolen cloth, used for dresses, cloaks, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thibetian</ent>⟦br⟧
